190bool CBBFinishArray(CBB *cbb, Array<uint8_t> *out) {
191 uint8_t *ptr;
192 size_t len;
193 if (!CBB_finish(cbb, &ptr, &len)) {
194 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_INTERNAL_ERROR);
195 return false;
196 }
197 out->Reset(ptr, len);
198 return true;
199}

201void ssl_reset_error_state(SSL *ssl) {
202 // Functions which use |SSL_get_error| must reset I/O and error state on
203 // entry.
204 ssl->s3->rwstate = SSL_ERROR_NONE;
205 ERR_clear_error();
206 ERR_clear_system_error();
207}
208
209void ssl_set_read_error(SSL* ssl) {
210 ssl->s3->read_shutdown = ssl_shutdown_error;
211 ssl->s3->read_error.reset(ERR_save_state());
212}
213
214static bool check_read_error(const SSL *ssl) {
215 if (ssl->s3->read_shutdown == ssl_shutdown_error) {
216 ERR_restore_state(ssl->s3->read_error.get());
217 return false;
218 }
219 return true;
220}

222bool ssl_can_write(const SSL *ssl) {
223 return !SSL_in_init(ssl) || ssl->s3->hs->can_early_write;
224}

226bool ssl_can_read(const SSL *ssl) {
227 return !SSL_in_init(ssl) || ssl->s3->hs->can_early_read;
228}

230ssl_open_record_t ssl_open_handshake(SSL *ssl, size_t *out_consumed,
231 uint8_t *out_alert, Span<uint8_t> in) {
232 *out_consumed = 0;
233 if (!check_read_error(ssl)) {
234 *out_alert = 0;
235 return ssl_open_record_error;
236 }
237 auto ret = ssl->method->open_handshake(ssl, out_consumed, out_alert, in);
238 if (ret == ssl_open_record_error) {
239 ssl_set_read_error(ssl);
240 }
241 return ret;
242}
243
244ssl_open_record_t ssl_open_change_cipher_spec(SSL *ssl, size_t *out_consumed,
245 uint8_t *out_alert,
246 Span<uint8_t> in) {
247 *out_consumed = 0;
248 if (!check_read_error(ssl)) {
249 *out_alert = 0;
250 return ssl_open_record_error;
251 }
252 auto ret =
253 ssl->method->open_change_cipher_spec(ssl, out_consumed, out_alert, in);
254 if (ret == ssl_open_record_error) {
255 ssl_set_read_error(ssl);
256 }
257 return ret;
258}

260ssl_open_record_t ssl_open_app_data(SSL *ssl, Span<uint8_t> *out,
261 size_t *out_consumed, uint8_t *out_alert,
262 Span<uint8_t> in) {
263 *out_consumed = 0;
264 if (!check_read_error(ssl)) {
265 *out_alert = 0;
266 return ssl_open_record_error;
267 }
268 auto ret = ssl->method->open_app_data(ssl, out, out_consumed, out_alert, in);
269 if (ret == ssl_open_record_error) {
270 ssl_set_read_error(ssl);
271 }
272 return ret;
273}

275void ssl_update_cache(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, int mode) {
276 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
277 SSL_CTX *ctx = ssl->session_ctx.get();
278 if (!SSL_SESSION_is_resumable(ssl->s3->established_session.get()) ||
279 (ctx->session_cache_mode & mode) != mode) {
280 return;
281 }
282
283 // Clients never use the internal session cache.
284 int use_internal_cache = ssl->server && !(ctx->session_cache_mode &
285 SSL_SESS_CACHE_NO_INTERNAL_STORE);
286
287 // A client may see new sessions on abbreviated handshakes if the server
288 // decides to renew the ticket. Once the handshake is completed, it should be
289 // inserted into the cache.
290 if (ssl->s3->established_session.get() != ssl->session.get() ||
291 (!ssl->server && hs->ticket_expected)) {
292 if (use_internal_cache) {
293 SSL_CTX_add_session(ctx, ssl->s3->established_session.get());
294 }
295 if (ctx->new_session_cb != NULL) {
296 UniquePtr<SSL_SESSION> ref = UpRef(ssl->s3->established_session);
297 if (ctx->new_session_cb(ssl, ref.get())) {
298 // |new_session_cb|'s return value signals whether it took ownership.
299 ref.release();
300 }
301 }
302 }
303
304 if (use_internal_cache &&
305 !(ctx->session_cache_mode & SSL_SESS_CACHE_NO_AUTO_CLEAR)) {
306 // Automatically flush the internal session cache every 255 connections.
307 int flush_cache = 0;
308 CRYPTO_MUTEX_lock_write(&ctx->lock);
309 ctx->handshakes_since_cache_flush++;
310 if (ctx->handshakes_since_cache_flush >= 255) {
311 flush_cache = 1;
312 ctx->handshakes_since_cache_flush = 0;
313 }
314 CRYPTO_MUTEX_unlock_write(&ctx->lock);
315
316 if (flush_cache) {
317 struct OPENSSL_timeval now;
318 ssl_get_current_time(ssl, &now);
319 SSL_CTX_flush_sessions(ctx, now.tv_sec);
320 }
321 }
322}

324static bool cbb_add_hex(CBB *cbb, Span<const uint8_t> in) {
325 static const char hextable[] = "0123456789abcdef";
326 uint8_t *out;
327
328 if (!CBB_add_space(cbb, &out, in.size() * 2)) {
329 return false;
330 }
331
332 for (uint8_t b : in) {
333 *(out++) = (uint8_t)hextable[b >> 4];
334 *(out++) = (uint8_t)hextable[b & 0xf];
335 }
336
337 return true;
338}

340bool ssl_log_secret(const SSL *ssl, const char *label,
341 Span<const uint8_t> secret) {
342 if (ssl->ctx->keylog_callback == NULL) {
343 return true;
344 }
345
346 ScopedCBB cbb;
347 Array<uint8_t> line;
348 if (!CBB_init(cbb.get(), strlen(label) + 1 + SSL3_RANDOM_SIZE * 2 + 1 +
349 secret.size() * 2 + 1) ||
350 !CBB_add_bytes(cbb.get(), reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t *>(label),
351 strlen(label)) ||
352 !CBB_add_u8(cbb.get(), ' ') ||
353 !cbb_add_hex(cbb.get(), ssl->s3->client_random) ||
354 !CBB_add_u8(cbb.get(), ' ') ||
355 !cbb_add_hex(cbb.get(), secret) ||
356 !CBB_add_u8(cbb.get(), 0 /* NUL */) ||
357 !CBBFinishArray(cbb.get(), &line)) {
358 return false;
359 }
360
361 ssl->ctx->keylog_callback(ssl, reinterpret_cast<const char *>(line.data()));
362 return true;
363}

365void ssl_do_info_callback(const SSL *ssl, int type, int value) {
366 void (*cb)(const SSL *ssl, int type, int value) = NULL;
367 if (ssl->info_callback != NULL) {
368 cb = ssl->info_callback;
369 } else if (ssl->ctx->info_callback != NULL) {
370 cb = ssl->ctx->info_callback;
371 }
372
373 if (cb != NULL) {
374 cb(ssl, type, value);
375 }
376}
377
378void ssl_do_msg_callback(const SSL *ssl, int is_write, int content_type,
379 Span<const uint8_t> in) {
380 if (ssl->msg_callback == NULL) {
381 return;
382 }
383
384 // |version| is zero when calling for |SSL3_RT_HEADER| and |SSL2_VERSION| for
385 // a V2ClientHello.
386 int version;
387 switch (content_type) {
388 case 0:
389 // V2ClientHello
390 version = SSL2_VERSION;
391 break;
392 case SSL3_RT_HEADER:
393 version = 0;
394 break;
395 default:
396 version = SSL_version(ssl);
397 }
398
399 ssl->msg_callback(is_write, version, content_type, in.data(), in.size(),
400 const_cast<SSL *>(ssl), ssl->msg_callback_arg);
401}

403void ssl_get_current_time(const SSL *ssl, struct OPENSSL_timeval *out_clock) {
404 // TODO(martinkr): Change callers to |ssl_ctx_get_current_time| and drop the
405 // |ssl| arg from |current_time_cb| if possible.
406 ssl_ctx_get_current_time(ssl->ctx.get(), out_clock);
407}
408
409void ssl_ctx_get_current_time(const SSL_CTX *ctx,
410 struct OPENSSL_timeval *out_clock) {
411 if (ctx->current_time_cb != NULL) {
412 // TODO(davidben): Update current_time_cb to use OPENSSL_timeval. See
413 // https://crbug.com/boringssl/155.
414 struct timeval clock;
415 ctx->current_time_cb(nullptr /* ssl */, &clock);
416 if (clock.tv_sec < 0) {
417 assert(0);
418 out_clock->tv_sec = 0;
419 out_clock->tv_usec = 0;
420 } else {
421 out_clock->tv_sec = (uint64_t)clock.tv_sec;
422 out_clock->tv_usec = (uint32_t)clock.tv_usec;
423 }
424 return;
425 }
426
427#if defined(BORINGSSL_UNSAFE_DETERMINISTIC_MODE)
428 out_clock->tv_sec = 1234;
429 out_clock->tv_usec = 1234;
430#elif defined(OPENSSL_WINDOWS)
431 struct _timeb time;
432 _ftime(&time);
433 if (time.time < 0) {
434 assert(0);
435 out_clock->tv_sec = 0;
436 out_clock->tv_usec = 0;
437 } else {
438 out_clock->tv_sec = time.time;
439 out_clock->tv_usec = time.millitm * 1000;
440 }
441#else
442 struct timeval clock;
443 gettimeofday(&clock, NULL);
444 if (clock.tv_sec < 0) {
445 assert(0);
446 out_clock->tv_sec = 0;
447 out_clock->tv_usec = 0;
448 } else {
449 out_clock->tv_sec = (uint64_t)clock.tv_sec;
450 out_clock->tv_usec = (uint32_t)clock.tv_usec;
451 }
452#endif
453}

459static bool ssl_can_renegotiate(const SSL *ssl) {
460 if (ssl->server || SSL_is_dtls(ssl)) {
461 return false;
462 }
463
464 if (ssl->s3->have_version &&
465 ssl_protocol_version(ssl) >= TLS1_3_VERSION) {
466 return false;
467 }
468
469 // The config has already been shed.
470 if (!ssl->config) {
471 return false;
472 }
473
474 switch (ssl->renegotiate_mode) {
475 case ssl_renegotiate_ignore:
476 case ssl_renegotiate_never:
477 return false;
478
479 case ssl_renegotiate_freely:
480 case ssl_renegotiate_explicit:
481 return true;
482 case ssl_renegotiate_once:
483 return ssl->s3->total_renegotiations == 0;
484 }
485
486 assert(0);
487 return false;
488}
489
490static void ssl_maybe_shed_handshake_config(SSL *ssl) {
491 if (ssl->s3->hs != nullptr ||
492 ssl->config == nullptr ||
493 !ssl->config->shed_handshake_config ||
494 ssl_can_renegotiate(ssl)) {
495 return;
496 }
497
498 ssl->config.reset();
499}

501void SSL_set_handoff_mode(SSL *ssl, bool on) {
502 if (!ssl->config) {
503 return;
504 }
505 ssl->config->handoff = on;
506}

508bool SSL_get_traffic_secrets(const SSL *ssl,
509 Span<const uint8_t> *out_read_traffic_secret,
510 Span<const uint8_t> *out_write_traffic_secret) {
511 if (SSL_version(ssl) < TLS1_3_VERSION) {
512 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_WRONG_SSL_VERSION);
513 return false;
514 }
515
516 if (!ssl->s3->initial_handshake_complete) {
517 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_HANDSHAKE_NOT_COMPLETE);
518 return false;
519 }
520
521 *out_read_traffic_secret = Span<const uint8_t>(
522 ssl->s3->read_traffic_secret, ssl->s3->read_traffic_secret_len);
523 *out_write_traffic_secret = Span<const uint8_t>(
524 ssl->s3->write_traffic_secret, ssl->s3->write_traffic_secret_len);
525
526 return true;
527}

543static uint32_t ssl_session_hash(const SSL_SESSION *sess) {
544 return ssl_hash_session_id(
545 MakeConstSpan(sess->session_id, sess->session_id_length));
546}
547
548static int ssl_session_cmp(const SSL_SESSION *a, const SSL_SESSION *b) {
549 if (a->session_id_length != b->session_id_length) {
550 return 1;
551 }
552
553 return OPENSSL_memcmp(a->session_id, b->session_id, a->session_id_length);
554}

572
573ssl_ctx_st::~ssl_ctx_st() {
574 // Free the internal session cache. Note that this calls the caller-supplied
575 // remove callback, so we must do it before clearing ex_data. (See ticket
576 // [openssl.org #212].)
577 SSL_CTX_flush_sessions(this, 0);
578
579 CRYPTO_free_ex_data(&g_ex_data_class_ssl_ctx, this, &ex_data);
580
581 CRYPTO_MUTEX_cleanup(&lock);
582 lh_SSL_SESSION_free(sessions);
583 x509_method->ssl_ctx_free(this);
584}
585
586SSL_CTX *SSL_CTX_new(const SSL_METHOD *method) {
587 if (method == NULL) {
588 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_NULL_SSL_METHOD_PASSED);
589 return nullptr;
590 }
591
592 UniquePtr<SSL_CTX> ret = MakeUnique<SSL_CTX>(method);
593 if (!ret) {
594 return nullptr;
595 }
596
597 ret->cert = MakeUnique<CERT>(method->x509_method);
598 ret->sessions = lh_SSL_SESSION_new(ssl_session_hash, ssl_session_cmp);
599 ret->client_CA.reset(sk_CRYPTO_BUFFER_new_null());
600 if (ret->cert == nullptr ||
601 ret->sessions == nullptr ||
602 ret->client_CA == nullptr ||
603 !ret->x509_method->ssl_ctx_new(ret.get())) {
604 return nullptr;
605 }
606
607 if (!SSL_CTX_set_strict_cipher_list(ret.get(), SSL_DEFAULT_CIPHER_LIST) ||
608 // Lock the SSL_CTX to the specified version, for compatibility with
609 // legacy uses of SSL_METHOD.
610 !SSL_CTX_set_max_proto_version(ret.get(), method->version) ||
611 !SSL_CTX_set_min_proto_version(ret.get(), method->version)) {
612 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_INTERNAL_ERROR);
613 return nullptr;
614 }
615
616 return ret.release();
617}
618
619int SSL_CTX_up_ref(SSL_CTX *ctx) {
620 CRYPTO_refcount_inc(&ctx->references);
621 return 1;
622}
623
624void SSL_CTX_free(SSL_CTX *ctx) {
625 if (ctx == NULL ||
626 !CRYPTO_refcount_dec_and_test_zero(&ctx->references)) {
627 return;
628 }
629
630 ctx->~ssl_ctx_st();
631 OPENSSL_free(ctx);
632}

649
650ssl_st::~ssl_st() {
651 CRYPTO_free_ex_data(&g_ex_data_class_ssl, this, &ex_data);
652 // |config| refers to |this|, so we must release it earlier.
653 config.reset();
654 if (method != NULL) {
655 method->ssl_free(this);
656 }
657}
658
659SSL *SSL_new(SSL_CTX *ctx) {
660 if (ctx == nullptr) {
661 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_NULL_SSL_CTX);
662 return nullptr;
663 }
664
665 UniquePtr<SSL> ssl = MakeUnique<SSL>(ctx);
666 if (ssl == nullptr) {
667 return nullptr;
668 }
669
670 ssl->config = MakeUnique<SSL_CONFIG>(ssl.get());
671 if (ssl->config == nullptr) {
672 return nullptr;
673 }
674 ssl->config->conf_min_version = ctx->conf_min_version;
675 ssl->config->conf_max_version = ctx->conf_max_version;
676
677 ssl->config->cert = ssl_cert_dup(ctx->cert.get());
678 if (ssl->config->cert == nullptr) {
679 return nullptr;
680 }
681
682 ssl->config->verify_mode = ctx->verify_mode;
683 ssl->config->verify_callback = ctx->default_verify_callback;
684 ssl->config->custom_verify_callback = ctx->custom_verify_callback;
685 ssl->config->retain_only_sha256_of_client_certs =
686 ctx->retain_only_sha256_of_client_certs;
687
688 if (!ssl->config->supported_group_list.CopyFrom(ctx->supported_group_list) ||
689 !ssl->config->alpn_client_proto_list.CopyFrom(
690 ctx->alpn_client_proto_list) ||
691 !ssl->config->verify_sigalgs.CopyFrom(ctx->verify_sigalgs)) {
692 return nullptr;
693 }
694
695 if (ctx->psk_identity_hint) {
696 ssl->config->psk_identity_hint.reset(
697 OPENSSL_strdup(ctx->psk_identity_hint.get()));
698 if (ssl->config->psk_identity_hint == nullptr) {
699 return nullptr;
700 }
701 }
702 ssl->config->psk_client_callback = ctx->psk_client_callback;
703 ssl->config->psk_server_callback = ctx->psk_server_callback;
704
705 ssl->config->channel_id_enabled = ctx->channel_id_enabled;
706 ssl->config->channel_id_private = UpRef(ctx->channel_id_private);
707
708 ssl->config->signed_cert_timestamps_enabled =
709 ctx->signed_cert_timestamps_enabled;
710 ssl->config->ocsp_stapling_enabled = ctx->ocsp_stapling_enabled;
711 ssl->config->handoff = ctx->handoff;
712 ssl->quic_method = ctx->quic_method;
713
714 if (!ssl->method->ssl_new(ssl.get()) ||
715 !ssl->ctx->x509_method->ssl_new(ssl->s3->hs.get())) {
716 return nullptr;
717 }
718
719 return ssl.release();
720}

764
765void SSL_set_bio(SSL *ssl, BIO *rbio, BIO *wbio) {
766 // For historical reasons, this function has many different cases in ownership
767 // handling.
768
769 // If nothing has changed, do nothing
770 if (rbio == SSL_get_rbio(ssl) && wbio == SSL_get_wbio(ssl)) {
771 return;
772 }
773
774 // If the two arguments are equal, one fewer reference is granted than
775 // taken.
776 if (rbio != NULL && rbio == wbio) {
777 BIO_up_ref(rbio);
778 }
779
780 // If only the wbio is changed, adopt only one reference.
781 if (rbio == SSL_get_rbio(ssl)) {
782 SSL_set0_wbio(ssl, wbio);
783 return;
784 }
785
786 // There is an asymmetry here for historical reasons. If only the rbio is
787 // changed AND the rbio and wbio were originally different, then we only adopt
788 // one reference.
789 if (wbio == SSL_get_wbio(ssl) && SSL_get_rbio(ssl) != SSL_get_wbio(ssl)) {
790 SSL_set0_rbio(ssl, rbio);
791 return;
792 }
793
794 // Otherwise, adopt both references.
795 SSL_set0_rbio(ssl, rbio);
796 SSL_set0_wbio(ssl, wbio);
797}

803size_t SSL_quic_max_handshake_flight_len(const SSL *ssl,
804 enum ssl_encryption_level_t level) {
805 // Limits flights to 16K by default when there are no large
806 // (certificate-carrying) messages.
807 static const size_t kDefaultLimit = 16384;
808
809 switch (level) {
810 case ssl_encryption_initial:
811 return kDefaultLimit;
812 case ssl_encryption_early_data:
813 // QUIC does not send EndOfEarlyData.
814 return 0;
815 case ssl_encryption_handshake:
816 if (ssl->server) {
817 // Servers may receive Certificate message if configured to request
818 // client certificates.
819 if (!!(ssl->config->verify_mode & SSL_VERIFY_PEER) &&
820 ssl->max_cert_list > kDefaultLimit) {
821 return ssl->max_cert_list;
822 }
823 } else {
824 // Clients may receive both Certificate message and a CertificateRequest
825 // message.
826 if (2*ssl->max_cert_list > kDefaultLimit) {
827 return 2*ssl->max_cert_list;
828 }
829 }
830 return kDefaultLimit;
831 case ssl_encryption_application:
832 // Note there is not actually a bound on the number of NewSessionTickets
833 // one may send in a row. This level may need more involved flow
834 // control. See https://github.com/quicwg/base-drafts/issues/1834.
835 return kDefaultLimit;
836 }
837
838 return 0;
839}

843}

846 return ssl->s3->write_level;

849int SSL_provide_quic_data(SSL *ssl, enum ssl_encryption_level_t level,
850 const uint8_t *data, size_t len) {
851 if (ssl->quic_method == nullptr) {
852 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_SHOULD_NOT_HAVE_BEEN_CALLED);
853 return 0;
854 }
855
856 if (level != ssl->s3->read_level) {
857 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_WRONG_ENCRYPTION_LEVEL_RECEIVED);
858 return 0;
859 }
860
861 size_t new_len = (ssl->s3->hs_buf ? ssl->s3->hs_buf->length : 0) + len;
862 if (new_len < len ||
863 new_len > SSL_quic_max_handshake_flight_len(ssl, level)) {
864 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_EXCESSIVE_MESSAGE_SIZE);
865 return 0;
866 }
867
868 return tls_append_handshake_data(ssl, MakeConstSpan(data, len));
869}
870
871int SSL_do_handshake(SSL *ssl) {
872 ssl_reset_error_state(ssl);
873
874 if (ssl->do_handshake == NULL) {
875 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_CONNECTION_TYPE_NOT_SET);
876 return -1;
877 }
878
879 if (!SSL_in_init(ssl)) {
880 return 1;
881 }
882
883 // Run the handshake.
884 SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs = ssl->s3->hs.get();
885
886 bool early_return = false;
887 int ret = ssl_run_handshake(hs, &early_return);
888 ssl_do_info_callback(
889 ssl, ssl->server ? SSL_CB_ACCEPT_EXIT : SSL_CB_CONNECT_EXIT, ret);
890 if (ret <= 0) {
891 return ret;
892 }
893
894 // Destroy the handshake object if the handshake has completely finished.
895 if (!early_return) {
896 ssl->s3->hs.reset();
897 ssl_maybe_shed_handshake_config(ssl);
898 }
899
900 return 1;
901}

903int SSL_connect(SSL *ssl) {
904 if (ssl->do_handshake == NULL) {
905 // Not properly initialized yet
906 SSL_set_connect_state(ssl);
907 }
908
909 return SSL_do_handshake(ssl);
910}

921static int ssl_do_post_handshake(SSL *ssl, const SSLMessage &msg) {
922 if (ssl_protocol_version(ssl) >= TLS1_3_VERSION) {
923 return tls13_post_handshake(ssl, msg);
924 }
925
926 // Check for renegotiation on the server before parsing to use the correct
927 // error. Renegotiation is triggered by a different message for servers.
928 if (ssl->server) {
929 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_NO_RENEGOTIATION);
930 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_NO_RENEGOTIATION);
931 return 0;
932 }
933
934 if (msg.type != SSL3_MT_HELLO_REQUEST || CBS_len(&msg.body) != 0) {
935 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR);
936 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_BAD_HELLO_REQUEST);
937 return 0;
938 }
939
940 if (ssl->renegotiate_mode == ssl_renegotiate_ignore) {
941 return 1; // Ignore the HelloRequest.
942 }
943
944 ssl->s3->renegotiate_pending = true;
945 if (ssl->renegotiate_mode == ssl_renegotiate_explicit) {
946 return 1; // Handle it later.
947 }
948
949 if (!SSL_renegotiate(ssl)) {
950 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_NO_RENEGOTIATION);
951 return 0;
952 }
953
954 return 1;
955}
956
957int SSL_process_quic_post_handshake(SSL *ssl) {
958 ssl_reset_error_state(ssl);
959
960 if (SSL_in_init(ssl)) {
961 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_SHOULD_NOT_HAVE_BEEN_CALLED);
962 return 0;
963 }
964
965 // Replay post-handshake message errors.
966 if (!check_read_error(ssl)) {
967 return 0;
968 }
969
970 // Process any buffered post-handshake messages.
971 SSLMessage msg;
972 while (ssl->method->get_message(ssl, &msg)) {
973 // Handle the post-handshake message and try again.
974 if (!ssl_do_post_handshake(ssl, msg)) {
975 ssl_set_read_error(ssl);
976 return 0;
977 }
978 ssl->method->next_message(ssl);
979 }
980
981 return 1;
982}
983
984static int ssl_read_impl(SSL *ssl) {
985 ssl_reset_error_state(ssl);
986
987 if (ssl->do_handshake == NULL) {
988 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_UNINITIALIZED);
989 return -1;
990 }
991
992 // Replay post-handshake message errors.
993 if (!check_read_error(ssl)) {
994 return -1;
995 }
996
997 while (ssl->s3->pending_app_data.empty()) {
998 if (ssl->s3->renegotiate_pending) {
999 ssl->s3->rwstate = SSL_ERROR_WANT_RENEGOTIATE;
1000 return -1;
1001 }
1002
1003 // Complete the current handshake, if any. False Start will cause
1004 // |SSL_do_handshake| to return mid-handshake, so this may require multiple
1005 // iterations.
1006 while (!ssl_can_read(ssl)) {
1007 int ret = SSL_do_handshake(ssl);
1008 if (ret < 0) {
1009 return ret;
1010 }
1011 if (ret == 0) {
1012 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_SSL_HANDSHAKE_FAILURE);
1013 return -1;
1014 }
1015 }
1016
1017 // Process any buffered post-handshake messages.
1018 SSLMessage msg;
1019 if (ssl->method->get_message(ssl, &msg)) {
1020 // If we received an interrupt in early read (EndOfEarlyData), loop again
1021 // for the handshake to process it.
1022 if (SSL_in_init(ssl)) {
1023 ssl->s3->hs->can_early_read = false;
1024 continue;
1025 }
1026
1027 // Handle the post-handshake message and try again.
1028 if (!ssl_do_post_handshake(ssl, msg)) {
1029 ssl_set_read_error(ssl);
1030 return -1;
1031 }
1032 ssl->method->next_message(ssl);
1033 continue; // Loop again. We may have begun a new handshake.
1034 }
1035
1036 uint8_t alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
1037 size_t consumed = 0;
1038 auto ret = ssl_open_app_data(ssl, &ssl->s3->pending_app_data, &consumed,
1039 &alert, ssl->s3->read_buffer.span());
1040 bool retry;
1041 int bio_ret = ssl_handle_open_record(ssl, &retry, ret, consumed, alert);
1042 if (bio_ret <= 0) {
1043 return bio_ret;
1044 }
1045 if (!retry) {
1046 assert(!ssl->s3->pending_app_data.empty());
1047 ssl->s3->key_update_count = 0;
1048 }
1049 }
1050
1051 return 1;
1052}
1053
1054int SSL_read(SSL *ssl, void *buf, int num) {
1055 int ret = SSL_peek(ssl, buf, num);
1056 if (ret <= 0) {
1057 return ret;
1058 }
1059 // TODO(davidben): In DTLS, should the rest of the record be discarded? DTLS
1060 // is not a stream. See https://crbug.com/boringssl/65.
1061 ssl->s3->pending_app_data =
1062 ssl->s3->pending_app_data.subspan(static_cast<size_t>(ret));
1063 if (ssl->s3->pending_app_data.empty()) {
1064 ssl->s3->read_buffer.DiscardConsumed();
1065 }
1066 return ret;
1067}
1068
1069int SSL_peek(SSL *ssl, void *buf, int num) {
1070 if (ssl->quic_method != nullptr) {
1071 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_SHOULD_NOT_HAVE_BEEN_CALLED);
1072 return 0;
1073 }
1074
1075 int ret = ssl_read_impl(ssl);
1076 if (ret <= 0) {
1077 return ret;
1078 }
1079 if (num <= 0) {
1080 return num;
1081 }
1082 size_t todo =
1083 std::min(ssl->s3->pending_app_data.size(), static_cast<size_t>(num));
1084 OPENSSL_memcpy(buf, ssl->s3->pending_app_data.data(), todo);
1085 return static_cast<int>(todo);
1086}
1087
1088int SSL_write(SSL *ssl, const void *buf, int num) {
1089 ssl_reset_error_state(ssl);
1090
1091 if (ssl->quic_method != nullptr) {
1092 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_SHOULD_NOT_HAVE_BEEN_CALLED);
1093 return 0;
1094 }
1095
1096 if (ssl->do_handshake == NULL) {
1097 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_UNINITIALIZED);
1098 return -1;
1099 }
1100
1101 if (ssl->s3->write_shutdown != ssl_shutdown_none) {
1102 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_PROTOCOL_IS_SHUTDOWN);
1103 return -1;
1104 }
1105
1106 int ret = 0;
1107 bool needs_handshake = false;
1108 do {
1109 // If necessary, complete the handshake implicitly.
1110 if (!ssl_can_write(ssl)) {
1111 ret = SSL_do_handshake(ssl);
1112 if (ret < 0) {
1113 return ret;
1114 }
1115 if (ret == 0) {
1116 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_SSL_HANDSHAKE_FAILURE);
1117 return -1;
1118 }
1119 }
1120
1121 ret = ssl->method->write_app_data(ssl, &needs_handshake,
1122 (const uint8_t *)buf, num);
1123 } while (needs_handshake);
1124 return ret;
1125}

1127int SSL_key_update(SSL *ssl, int request_type) {
1128 ssl_reset_error_state(ssl);
1129
1130 if (ssl->do_handshake == NULL) {
1131 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_UNINITIALIZED);
1132 return 0;
1133 }
1134
1135 if (ssl->ctx->quic_method != nullptr) {
1136 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_SHOULD_NOT_HAVE_BEEN_CALLED);
1137 return 0;
1138 }
1139
1140 if (!ssl->s3->initial_handshake_complete) {
1141 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_HANDSHAKE_NOT_COMPLETE);
1142 return 0;
1143 }
1144
1145 if (ssl_protocol_version(ssl) < TLS1_3_VERSION) {
1146 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_WRONG_SSL_VERSION);
1147 return 0;
1148 }
1149
1150 if (!ssl->s3->key_update_pending &&
1151 !tls13_add_key_update(ssl, request_type)) {
1152 return 0;
1153 }
1154
1155 return 1;
1156}

1158int SSL_shutdown(SSL *ssl) {
1159 ssl_reset_error_state(ssl);
1160
1161 if (ssl->do_handshake == NULL) {
1162 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_UNINITIALIZED);
1163 return -1;
1164 }
1165
1166 // If we are in the middle of a handshake, silently succeed. Consumers often
1167 // call this function before |SSL_free|, whether the handshake succeeded or
1168 // not. We assume the caller has already handled failed handshakes.
1169 if (SSL_in_init(ssl)) {
1170 return 1;
1171 }
1172
1173 if (ssl->quiet_shutdown) {
1174 // Do nothing if configured not to send a close_notify.
1175 ssl->s3->write_shutdown = ssl_shutdown_close_notify;
1176 ssl->s3->read_shutdown = ssl_shutdown_close_notify;
1177 return 1;
1178 }
1179
1180 // This function completes in two stages. It sends a close_notify and then it
1181 // waits for a close_notify to come in. Perform exactly one action and return
1182 // whether or not it succeeds.
1183
1184 if (ssl->s3->write_shutdown != ssl_shutdown_close_notify) {
1185 // Send a close_notify.
1186 if (ssl_send_alert_impl(ssl, SSL3_AL_WARNING, SSL_AD_CLOSE_NOTIFY) <= 0) {
1187 return -1;
1188 }
1189 } else if (ssl->s3->alert_dispatch) {
1190 // Finish sending the close_notify.
1191 if (ssl->method->dispatch_alert(ssl) <= 0) {
1192 return -1;
1193 }
1194 } else if (ssl->s3->read_shutdown != ssl_shutdown_close_notify) {
1195 if (SSL_is_dtls(ssl)) {
1196 // Bidirectional shutdown doesn't make sense for an unordered
1197 // transport. DTLS alerts also aren't delivered reliably, so we may even
1198 // time out because the peer never received our close_notify. Report to
1199 // the caller that the channel has fully shut down.
1200 if (ssl->s3->read_shutdown == ssl_shutdown_error) {
1201 ERR_restore_state(ssl->s3->read_error.get());
1202 return -1;
1203 }
1204 ssl->s3->read_shutdown = ssl_shutdown_close_notify;
1205 } else {
1206 // Process records until an error, close_notify, or application data.
1207 if (ssl_read_impl(ssl) > 0) {
1208 // We received some unexpected application data.
1209 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_APPLICATION_DATA_ON_SHUTDOWN);
1210 return -1;
1211 }
1212 if (ssl->s3->read_shutdown != ssl_shutdown_close_notify) {
1213 return -1;
1214 }
1215 }
1216 }
1217
1218 // Return 0 for unidirectional shutdown and 1 for bidirectional shutdown.
1219 return ssl->s3->read_shutdown == ssl_shutdown_close_notify;
1220}
1221
1222int SSL_send_fatal_alert(SSL *ssl, uint8_t alert) {
1223 if (ssl->s3->alert_dispatch) {
1224 if (ssl->s3->send_alert[0] != SSL3_AL_FATAL ||
1225 ssl->s3->send_alert[1] != alert) {
1226 // We are already attempting to write a different alert.
1227 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_PROTOCOL_IS_SHUTDOWN);
1228 return -1;
1229 }
1230 return ssl->method->dispatch_alert(ssl);
1231 }
1232
1233 return ssl_send_alert_impl(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, alert);
1234}

1274void SSL_reset_early_data_reject(SSL *ssl) {

1277 hs->wait != ssl_hs_early_data_rejected) {

1299 case ssl_early_data_disabled:
1300 return "disabled";
1301 case ssl_early_data_accepted:

1305 case ssl_early_data_peer_declined:

1308 return "no_session_offered";

1310 return "session_not_resumed";

1315 case ssl_early_data_alpn_mismatch:
1316 return "alpn_mismatch";
1317 case ssl_early_data_channel_id:
1318 return "channel_id";
1319 case ssl_early_data_token_binding:
1320 return "token_binding";
1321 case ssl_early_data_ticket_age_skew:
1322 return "ticket_age_skew";
1323 case ssl_early_data_quic_parameter_mismatch:
1324 return "quic_parameter_mismatch";
1325 case ssl_early_data_alps_mismatch:
1326 return "alps_mismatch";
1327 }
1328
1329 return nullptr;
1330}
1331
1332static int bio_retry_reason_to_error(int reason) {
1333 switch (reason) {
1334 case BIO_RR_CONNECT:
1335 return SSL_ERROR_WANT_CONNECT;
1336 case BIO_RR_ACCEPT:
1337 return SSL_ERROR_WANT_ACCEPT;
1338 default:
1339 return SSL_ERROR_SYSCALL;
1340 }
1341}
1342
1343int SSL_get_error(const SSL *ssl, int ret_code) {
1344 if (ret_code > 0) {
1345 return SSL_ERROR_NONE;
1346 }
1347
1348 // Make things return SSL_ERROR_SYSCALL when doing SSL_do_handshake etc,
1349 // where we do encode the error
1350 uint32_t err = ERR_peek_error();
1351 if (err != 0) {
1352 if (ERR_GET_LIB(err) == ERR_LIB_SYS) {
1353 return SSL_ERROR_SYSCALL;
1354 }
1355 return SSL_ERROR_SSL;
1356 }
1357
1358 if (ret_code == 0) {
1359 if (ssl->s3->read_shutdown == ssl_shutdown_close_notify) {
1360 return SSL_ERROR_ZERO_RETURN;
1361 }
1362 // An EOF was observed which violates the protocol, and the underlying
1363 // transport does not participate in the error queue. Bubble up to the
1364 // caller.
1365 return SSL_ERROR_SYSCALL;
1366 }
1367
1368 switch (ssl->s3->rwstate) {
1369 case SSL_ERROR_PENDING_SESSION:
1370 case SSL_ERROR_PENDING_CERTIFICATE:
1371 case SSL_ERROR_HANDOFF:
1372 case SSL_ERROR_HANDBACK:
1373 case SSL_ERROR_WANT_X509_LOOKUP:
1374 case SSL_ERROR_WANT_CHANNEL_ID_LOOKUP:
1375 case SSL_ERROR_WANT_PRIVATE_KEY_OPERATION:
1376 case SSL_ERROR_PENDING_TICKET:
1377 case SSL_ERROR_EARLY_DATA_REJECTED:
1378 case SSL_ERROR_WANT_CERTIFICATE_VERIFY:
1379 case SSL_ERROR_WANT_RENEGOTIATE:
1380 case SSL_ERROR_HANDSHAKE_HINTS_READY:
1381 return ssl->s3->rwstate;
1382
1383 case SSL_ERROR_WANT_READ: {
1384 if (ssl->quic_method) {
1385 return SSL_ERROR_WANT_READ;
1386 }
1387 BIO *bio = SSL_get_rbio(ssl);
1388 if (BIO_should_read(bio)) {
1389 return SSL_ERROR_WANT_READ;
1390 }
1391
1392 if (BIO_should_write(bio)) {
1393 // TODO(davidben): OpenSSL historically checked for writes on the read
1394 // BIO. Can this be removed?
1395 return SSL_ERROR_WANT_WRITE;
1396 }
1397
1398 if (BIO_should_io_special(bio)) {
1399 return bio_retry_reason_to_error(BIO_get_retry_reason(bio));
1400 }
1401
1402 break;
1403 }
1404
1405 case SSL_ERROR_WANT_WRITE: {
1406 BIO *bio = SSL_get_wbio(ssl);
1407 if (BIO_should_write(bio)) {
1408 return SSL_ERROR_WANT_WRITE;
1409 }
1410
1411 if (BIO_should_read(bio)) {
1412 // TODO(davidben): OpenSSL historically checked for reads on the write
1413 // BIO. Can this be removed?
1414 return SSL_ERROR_WANT_READ;
1415 }
1416
1417 if (BIO_should_io_special(bio)) {
1418 return bio_retry_reason_to_error(BIO_get_retry_reason(bio));
1419 }
1420
1421 break;
1422 }
1423 }
1424
1425 return SSL_ERROR_SYSCALL;
1426}

1532int SSL_get_tls_unique(const SSL *ssl, uint8_t *out, size_t *out_len,
1533 size_t max_out) {
1534 *out_len = 0;
1535 OPENSSL_memset(out, 0, max_out);
1536
1537 // tls-unique is not defined for TLS 1.3.
1538 if (!ssl->s3->initial_handshake_complete ||
1539 ssl_protocol_version(ssl) >= TLS1_3_VERSION) {
1540 return 0;
1541 }
1542
1543 // The tls-unique value is the first Finished message in the handshake, which
1544 // is the client's in a full handshake and the server's for a resumption. See
1545 // https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5929#section-3.1.
1546 const uint8_t *finished = ssl->s3->previous_client_finished;
1547 size_t finished_len = ssl->s3->previous_client_finished_len;
1548 if (ssl->session != NULL) {
1549 // tls-unique is broken for resumed sessions unless EMS is used.
1550 if (!ssl->session->extended_master_secret) {
1551 return 0;
1552 }
1553 finished = ssl->s3->previous_server_finished;
1554 finished_len = ssl->s3->previous_server_finished_len;
1555 }
1556
1557 *out_len = finished_len;
1558 if (finished_len > max_out) {
1559 *out_len = max_out;
1560 }
1561
1562 OPENSSL_memcpy(out, finished, *out_len);
1563 return 1;
1564}

1566static int set_session_id_context(CERT *cert, const uint8_t *sid_ctx,
1567 size_t sid_ctx_len) {
1568 if (sid_ctx_len > sizeof(cert->sid_ctx)) {

1629int SSL_set_fd(SSL *ssl, int fd) {
1630 BIO *bio = BIO_new(BIO_s_socket());
1631 if (bio == NULL) {
1632 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_BUF_LIB);
1633 return 0;
1634 }

1636 SSL_set_bio(ssl, bio, bio);
1637 return 1;
1638}
1639
1640int SSL_set_wfd(SSL *ssl, int fd) {
1641 BIO *rbio = SSL_get_rbio(ssl);
1642 if (rbio == NULL || BIO_method_type(rbio) != BIO_TYPE_SOCKET ||
1643 BIO_get_fd(rbio, NULL) != fd) {
1644 BIO *bio = BIO_new(BIO_s_socket());
1645 if (bio == NULL) {
1646 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_BUF_LIB);
1647 return 0;
1648 }
1649 BIO_set_fd(bio, fd, BIO_NOCLOSE);
1650 SSL_set0_wbio(ssl, bio);
1651 } else {
1652 // Copy the rbio over to the wbio.
1653 BIO_up_ref(rbio);
1654 SSL_set0_wbio(ssl, rbio);
1655 }
1656
1657 return 1;
1658}

1726int SSL_get_extms_support(const SSL *ssl) {
1727 // TLS 1.3 does not require extended master secret and always reports as
1728 // supporting it.
1729 if (!ssl->s3->have_version) {
1730 return 0;
1731 }
1732 if (ssl_protocol_version(ssl) >= TLS1_3_VERSION) {
1733 return 1;
1734 }
1735
1736 // If the initial handshake completed, query the established session.
1737 if (ssl->s3->established_session != NULL) {
1738 return ssl->s3->established_session->extended_master_secret;
1739 }
1740
1741 // Otherwise, query the in-progress handshake.
1742 if (ssl->s3->hs != NULL) {
1743 return ssl->s3->hs->extended_master_secret;
1744 }
1745 assert(0);
1746 return 0;
1747}

1778int SSL_renegotiate(SSL *ssl) {
1779 // Caller-initiated renegotiation is not supported.
1780 if (!ssl->s3->renegotiate_pending) {
1781 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_SHOULD_NOT_HAVE_BEEN_CALLED);
1782 return 0;
1783 }
1784
1785 if (!ssl_can_renegotiate(ssl)) {
1786 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_NO_RENEGOTIATION);
1787 return 0;
1788 }
1789
1790 // We should not have told the caller to release the private key.
1791 assert(!SSL_can_release_private_key(ssl));
1792
1793 // Renegotiation is only supported at quiescent points in the application
1794 // protocol, namely in HTTPS, just before reading the HTTP response.
1795 // Require the record-layer be idle and avoid complexities of sending a
1796 // handshake record while an application_data record is being written.
1797 if (!ssl->s3->write_buffer.empty() ||
1798 ssl->s3->write_shutdown != ssl_shutdown_none) {
1799 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_NO_RENEGOTIATION);
1800 return 0;
1801 }
1802
1803 // Begin a new handshake.
1804 if (ssl->s3->hs != nullptr) {
1805 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_INTERNAL_ERROR);
1806 return 0;
1807 }
1808 ssl->s3->hs = ssl_handshake_new(ssl);
1809 if (ssl->s3->hs == nullptr) {
1810 return 0;
1811 }
1812
1813 ssl->s3->renegotiate_pending = false;
1814 ssl->s3->total_renegotiations++;
1815 return 1;
1816}

1819 return SSL_in_init(ssl) && ssl->s3->initial_handshake_complete;
1820}

1914int SSL_CTX_get_tlsext_ticket_keys(SSL_CTX *ctx, void *out, size_t len) {
1915 if (out == NULL) {
1916 return 48;
1917 }
1918 if (len != 48) {
1919 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_INVALID_TICKET_KEYS_LENGTH);
1920 return 0;
1921 }
1922
1923 // The default ticket keys are initialized lazily. Trigger a key
1924 // rotation to initialize them.
1925 if (!ssl_ctx_rotate_ticket_encryption_key(ctx)) {
1926 return 0;
1927 }
1928
1929 uint8_t *out_bytes = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t *>(out);
1930 MutexReadLock lock(&ctx->lock);
1931 OPENSSL_memcpy(out_bytes, ctx->ticket_key_current->name, 16);
1932 OPENSSL_memcpy(out_bytes + 16, ctx->ticket_key_current->hmac_key, 16);
1933 OPENSSL_memcpy(out_bytes + 32, ctx->ticket_key_current->aes_key, 16);
1934 return 1;
1935}
1936
1937int SSL_CTX_set_tlsext_ticket_keys(SSL_CTX *ctx, const void *in, size_t len) {
1938 if (in == NULL) {
1939 return 48;
1940 }
1941 if (len != 48) {
1942 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_INVALID_TICKET_KEYS_LENGTH);
1943 return 0;
1944 }
1945 auto key = MakeUnique<TicketKey>();
1946 if (!key) {
1947 return 0;
1948 }
1949 const uint8_t *in_bytes = reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t *>(in);
1950 OPENSSL_memcpy(key->name, in_bytes, 16);
1951 OPENSSL_memcpy(key->hmac_key, in_bytes + 16, 16);
1952 OPENSSL_memcpy(key->aes_key, in_bytes + 32, 16);
1953 // Disable automatic key rotation for manually-configured keys. This is now
1954 // the caller's responsibility.
1955 key->next_rotation_tv_sec = 0;
1956 ctx->ticket_key_current = std::move(key);
1957 ctx->ticket_key_prev.reset();
1958 return 1;
1959}

2254int SSL_select_next_proto(uint8_t **out, uint8_t *out_len, const uint8_t *peer,
2255 unsigned peer_len, const uint8_t *supported,
2256 unsigned supported_len) {
2257 const uint8_t *result;
2258 int status;
2259
2260 // For each protocol in peer preference order, see if we support it.
2261 for (unsigned i = 0; i < peer_len;) {
2262 for (unsigned j = 0; j < supported_len;) {
2263 if (peer[i] == supported[j] &&
2264 OPENSSL_memcmp(&peer[i + 1], &supported[j + 1], peer[i]) == 0) {
2265 // We found a match
2266 result = &peer[i];
2267 status = OPENSSL_NPN_NEGOTIATED;
2268 goto found;
2269 }
2270 j += supported[j];
2271 j++;
2272 }
2273 i += peer[i];
2274 i++;
2275 }
2276
2277 // There's no overlap between our protocols and the peer's list.
2278 result = supported;
2279 status = OPENSSL_NPN_NO_OVERLAP;
2280
2281found:
2282 *out = (uint8_t *)result + 1;
2283 *out_len = result[0];
2284 return status;
2285}

2565void SSL_set_shutdown(SSL *ssl, int mode) {
2566 // It is an error to clear any bits that have already been set. (We can't try
2567 // to get a second close_notify or send two.)
2568 assert((SSL_get_shutdown(ssl) & mode) == SSL_get_shutdown(ssl));
2569
2570 if (mode & SSL_RECEIVED_SHUTDOWN &&
2571 ssl->s3->read_shutdown == ssl_shutdown_none) {
2572 ssl->s3->read_shutdown = ssl_shutdown_close_notify;
2573 }
2574
2575 if (mode & SSL_SENT_SHUTDOWN &&
2576 ssl->s3->write_shutdown == ssl_shutdown_none) {
2577 ssl->s3->write_shutdown = ssl_shutdown_close_notify;
2578 }
2579}
2580
2581int SSL_get_shutdown(const SSL *ssl) {
2582 int ret = 0;
2583 if (ssl->s3->read_shutdown != ssl_shutdown_none) {
2584 // Historically, OpenSSL set |SSL_RECEIVED_SHUTDOWN| on both close_notify
2585 // and fatal alert.
2586 ret |= SSL_RECEIVED_SHUTDOWN;
2587 }
2588 if (ssl->s3->write_shutdown == ssl_shutdown_close_notify) {
2589 // Historically, OpenSSL set |SSL_SENT_SHUTDOWN| on only close_notify.
2590 ret |= SSL_SENT_SHUTDOWN;
2591 }
2592 return ret;
2593}

2595SSL_CTX *SSL_get_SSL_CTX(const SSL *ssl) { return ssl->ctx.get(); }
2596
2597SSL_CTX *SSL_set_SSL_CTX(SSL *ssl, SSL_CTX *ctx) {
2598 if (!ssl->config) {
2599 return NULL;
2600 }
2601 if (ssl->ctx.get() == ctx) {
2602 return ssl->ctx.get();
2603 }
2604
2605 // One cannot change the X.509 callbacks during a connection.
2606 if (ssl->ctx->x509_method != ctx->x509_method) {
2607 assert(0);
2608 return NULL;
2609 }
2610
2611 UniquePtr<CERT> new_cert = ssl_cert_dup(ctx->cert.get());
2612 if (!new_cert) {
2613 return nullptr;
2614 }
2615
2616 ssl->config->cert = std::move(new_cert);
2617 ssl->ctx = UpRef(ctx);
2618 ssl->enable_early_data = ssl->ctx->enable_early_data;
2619
2620 return ssl->ctx.get();
2621}

2721static int use_psk_identity_hint(UniquePtr<char> *out,
2722 const char *identity_hint) {
2723 if (identity_hint != NULL && strlen(identity_hint) > PSK_MAX_IDENTITY_LEN) {
2724 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DATA_LENGTH_TOO_LONG);
2725 return 0;
2726 }
2727
2728 // Clear currently configured hint, if any.
2729 out->reset();
2730
2731 // Treat the empty hint as not supplying one. Plain PSK makes it possible to
2732 // send either no hint (omit ServerKeyExchange) or an empty hint, while
2733 // ECDHE_PSK can only spell empty hint. Having different capabilities is odd,
2734 // so we interpret empty and missing as identical.
2735 if (identity_hint != NULL && identity_hint[0] != '\0') {
2736 out->reset(OPENSSL_strdup(identity_hint));
2737 if (*out == nullptr) {
2738 return 0;
2739 }
2740 }
2741
2742 return 1;
2743}

2746 return use_psk_identity_hint(&ctx->psk_identity_hint, identity_hint);
2747}

2754}

2929static uint64_t be_to_u64(const uint8_t in[8]) {
2930 return (((uint64_t)in[0]) << 56) | (((uint64_t)in[1]) << 48) |
2931 (((uint64_t)in[2]) << 40) | (((uint64_t)in[3]) << 32) |
2932 (((uint64_t)in[4]) << 24) | (((uint64_t)in[5]) << 16) |
2933 (((uint64_t)in[6]) << 8) | ((uint64_t)in[7]);
2934}

2936uint64_t SSL_get_read_sequence(const SSL *ssl) {
2937 // TODO(davidben): Internally represent sequence numbers as uint64_t.
2938 if (SSL_is_dtls(ssl)) {
2939 // max_seq_num already includes the epoch.
2940 assert(ssl->d1->r_epoch == (ssl->d1->bitmap.max_seq_num >> 48));
2941 return ssl->d1->bitmap.max_seq_num;
2942 }
2943 return be_to_u64(ssl->s3->read_sequence);
2944}
2945
2946uint64_t SSL_get_write_sequence(const SSL *ssl) {
2947 uint64_t ret = be_to_u64(ssl->s3->write_sequence);
2948 if (SSL_is_dtls(ssl)) {
2949 assert((ret >> 48) == 0);
2950 ret |= ((uint64_t)ssl->d1->w_epoch) << 48;
2951 }
2952 return ret;
2953}

3044int SSL_clear(SSL *ssl) {
3045 if (!ssl->config) {
3046 return 0; // SSL_clear may not be used after shedding config.
3047 }
3048
3049 // In OpenSSL, reusing a client |SSL| with |SSL_clear| causes the previously
3050 // established session to be offered the next time around. wpa_supplicant
3051 // depends on this behavior, so emulate it.
3052 UniquePtr<SSL_SESSION> session;
3053 if (!ssl->server && ssl->s3->established_session != NULL) {
3054 session = UpRef(ssl->s3->established_session);
3055 }
3056
3057 // The ssl->d1->mtu is simultaneously configuration (preserved across
3058 // clear) and connection-specific state (gets reset).
3059 //
3060 // TODO(davidben): Avoid this.
3061 unsigned mtu = 0;
3062 if (ssl->d1 != NULL) {
3063 mtu = ssl->d1->mtu;
3064 }
3065
3066 ssl->method->ssl_free(ssl);
3067 if (!ssl->method->ssl_new(ssl)) {
3068 return 0;
3069 }
3070
3071 if (SSL_is_dtls(ssl) && (SSL_get_options(ssl) & SSL_OP_NO_QUERY_MTU)) {
3072 ssl->d1->mtu = mtu;
3073 }
3074
3075 if (session != nullptr) {
3076 SSL_set_session(ssl, session.get());
3077 }
3078
3079 return 1;
3080}

3129SSL_SESSION *SSL_process_tls13_new_session_ticket(SSL *ssl, const uint8_t *buf,
3130 size_t buf_len) {
3131 if (SSL_in_init(ssl) ||
3132 ssl_protocol_version(ssl) != TLS1_3_VERSION ||
3133 ssl->server) {
3134 // Only TLS 1.3 clients are supported.
3135 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_SHOULD_NOT_HAVE_BEEN_CALLED);
3136 return nullptr;
3137 }
3138
3139 CBS cbs, body;
3140 CBS_init(&cbs, buf, buf_len);
3141 uint8_t type;
3142 if (!CBS_get_u8(&cbs, &type) ||
3143 !CBS_get_u24_length_prefixed(&cbs, &body) ||
3144 CBS_len(&cbs) != 0) {
3145 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
3146 return nullptr;
3147 }
3148
3149 UniquePtr<SSL_SESSION> session = tls13_create_session_with_ticket(ssl, &body);
3150 if (!session) {
3151 // |tls13_create_session_with_ticket| puts the correct error.
3152 return nullptr;
3153 }
3154 return session.release();
3155}
